<IN>
BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)
</IN>
<LP>
   OTTAWA -- The Canadian government said it will offer 1.6
billion Canadian dollars (US$1.4 billion) of government bonds
in four maturities this week.
   The sale will involve 10.25% bonds due Feb. 1, 1994;
10.25% bonds due March 1, 1996; 10.5% bonds due March 1,
2001; 11.25% bonds due June 1, 2015. Offering terms are to be
announced today. The Bank of Canada agreed to purchase at
least C$100 million of the new bonds. The remainder will be
available to public investors.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Proceeds of the issue will be used to redeem C$1.1 billion
of government bonds maturing Oct. 1 and for general
government purposes.
