   United Companies Financial
</HL>
<DATE>
09/18/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
MORTGAGES, MORTGAGE BANKERS, MORTGAGE-BACKED SECURITIES (MOR)
</IN>
<GV>
FEDERAL GOVERNMENT (FDL)
</GV>
<LP>
   DALLAS -- United Companies Financial Corp. said it had
signed a definitive agreement with Foster Mortgage Corp. to
acquire substantially all of its assets.
   United Companies, based in Baton Rouge, La., is a
financial services holding company. Foster is a unit of
Benjamin Franklin Federal Savings Association, a
Houston-based thrift that is under the conservatorship of the
Resolution Trust Corp. The RTC has already approved the
transaction, United Companies said.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Foster currently services about $8 billion in mortgage
loans. United Companies said the acquisition closing date is
projected for Nov. 1, with the purchase price being based
primarily on the portfolio balances as of Oct. 31.
</TEXT>
