<LP>
   PITTSBURGH -- Cimflex Teknowledge Corp. said it has
completed the conversion of its diagnostics business into a
new high-technology company called Applied Diagnostics Inc.
   Applied Diagnostics is involved with troubleshooting
electronic circuit assemblies and certain types of
manufacturing equipment. Those products were developed by
Cimflex over the last three years through a research and
development financing agreement with PaineWebber R &amp; D
Partners L.P. The initial shareholders of Applied Diagnostics
are PaineWebber and Cimflex. Cimflex provides software and
integrated systems for factory management, automation and
control.
