</IN>
<LP>
   Financial Corp. of Santa Barbara said it filed for
protection under Chapter 11 of the federal Bankruptcy Code in
an attempt to "ensure an orderly disposition of the company's
remaining assets."
   The company's main asset, Santa Barbara Savings &amp; Loan
Association, was seized in April by federal regulators.
