</SO>
<CO>
   SREG
</CO>
<IN>
OFFICE EQUIPMENT (OFF)
</IN>
<LP>
   Standard Register Co., hurting from a weak general
economy, higher paper costs and tough competition in the
business-forms industry, said it expects lower third-quarter
and full-year earnings.
   The Dayton, Ohio, company also said it will begin a major
cost reduction program over the next six months, slashing
employment and closing several production facilities. The
company didn't elaborate. However, it said the program will
result in a one-time fourth-quarter charge. It didn't
disclose the amount.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Last year, the company earned $40.4 million, or $1.35 a
share, on revenue of $708.9 million. In last year's third
quarter, the company earned $7.5 million, or 25 cents a
share, on revenue of $174.1 million. In last year's fourth
quarter, the company earned $14.8 million, or 49 cents a
share, on revenue of $187.1 million.
