<LP>
   C. Itoh &amp; Co. Ltd., a major Japanese trading house, said
it will establish a finance joint venture in London with
Westinghouse Credit Corp. of the U.S. to engage in merchant
banking activities in Europe.
   The joint venture, European Capital Co. Ltd., will be
capitalized at #1 million ($1.9 million) and will formally
begin operations on Sept. 20. The joint venture will engage
in merchant banking activities such as project finance, trade
finance and merger and acquisition consulting.
