Securities Association (TSA) of the U.K.
   Tokyo-based C. Itoh will hold a 25% share in the venture
while Westinghouse Credit, a unit of Westinghouse Electric
Corp. of Pittsburgh, will have a 20% share.
   Century Leasing System Co. Ltd., a C. Itoh group member,
will hold a 5% share of the joint venture, while the
remaining 50% will be divided among roughly five European
executives.
   A C. Itoh spokesman said the parent companies are planning
to lend a total of seven billion yen ($51.1 million) to the
joint venture for trade finance.
